    "body": "> since your app itself is the one creating the browser windows\n\nthat premise is not correct in my case. I am developing [a module](https://github.com/yan-foto/electron-reload) which refreshes the contents of `BrowserWindow` upon any change in source files. The idea is to require this module and let the rest be done automatically. I prefer to avoid asking users (of the module) to emit an event everytime they create a `BrowserWindow`. Does it make sense or am I missing something here?\n"
